SIMPLE: outstand
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Outstand
<hw>Out*stand"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To stand out, or
project, from a surface or mass; hence, to remain standing
out.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outstand</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Outstand
<hw>Out*stand"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To resist
effectually; to withstand; to sustain without yielding.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Woodward.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To stay beyond.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧I have
<xex>outstood</xex> my time.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outstanding</ent>⟦br⟧
